The paper deals with a caching problem in device-to-device (D2D) networks with mobility, which involves offloading data from the network to devices. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including networked systems (cs.NI), distributed computing (cs.DC), information theory (cs.IT), control systems (cs.SY), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, given the focus on network optimization and mobility, cs.NI and cs.DC are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.IT, cs.SY, and cs.LG.
